# Fix #640: Stricli parsed flag string defaults bypass numberParser

## Finding

**This is not a bug.** Stricli's runtime at `node_modules/@stricli/core/dist/index.js:623` always passes `kind: "parsed"` flag defaults through `parse()`:

```js
return parseInput(externalFlagName, flag, flag.default, context);
```

So `numberParser("20")` → `20` (number). Commands receive the correct type at runtime.

This matches option 1 from the issue: "Verify Stricli's behavior: does it actually call `parse()` on the default? If so, this is a non-issue."

## Changes

### 1. Add regression test (`test/lib/command.test.ts`)

Insert after the test at line 169 ("captures flags as Sentry tags when command runs"). The existing test at line 124 runs `["test", "--verbose", "--limit", "50"]` (explicit flag). The new test runs `["test"]` (no flag, uses default) and asserts the value is `number 10`, not `string "10"`.

```typescript
test("passes string defaults through parse() — numberParser default is number at runtime", async () => {
  let receivedFlags: Record<string, unknown> | null = null;

  const command = buildCommand<{ limit: number }, [], TestContext>({
    auth: false,
    docs: { brief: "Test" },
    parameters: {
      flags: {
        limit: {
          kind: "parsed",
          parse: numberParser,
          brief: "Limit",
          default: "10",
        },
      },
    },
    // biome-ignore lint/correctness/useYield: test command — no output to yield
    async *func(this: TestContext, flags: { limit: number }) {
      receivedFlags = flags as unknown as Record<string, unknown>;
    },
  });

  const routeMap = buildRouteMap({
    routes: { test: command },
    docs: { brief: "Test app" },
  });
  const app = buildApplication(routeMap, { name: "test" });
  const ctx = createTestContext();

  // Run WITHOUT --limit to exercise the default path
  await run(app, ["test"], ctx as TestContext);

  expect(receivedFlags).not.toBeNull();
  expect(receivedFlags!.limit).toBe(10);
  expect(typeof receivedFlags!.limit).toBe("number");
});
```

